    pearls: ["The CRITICAL distinction: locked-in syndrome patients are FULLY CONSCIOUS and AWARE -- they can hear, see, feel, and think normally but cannot move or speak; they are NOT in a coma or vegetative state","Always test for voluntary vertical eye movements and purposeful blinking in any patient who appears comatose -- misdiagnosis of LIS as coma occurs in up to 50% of cases and can persist for weeks to months","The patient has FULL decisional capacity and must be included in all medical decisions -- use the established communication system to obtain informed consent, discuss treatment goals, and address care preferences","Central pontine myelinolysis is a PREVENTABLE cause of LIS: when correcting chronic hyponatremia, do not exceed 10-12 mEq/L per 24 hours; monitor sodium levels every 4-6 hours during correction","DVT and pulmonary embolism are major causes of mortality in LIS due to complete immobility -- ensure both pharmacological (heparin/LMWH) and mechanical (SCDs) prophylaxis are in place","Emotional support is paramount: the patient is trapped in a functional body and is fully aware of their devastating condition; assess for depression, facilitate communication with loved ones, and provide compassionate care"],
